{
    "response": "To compute the **sample variance** of the data set:\n\n$$\n\\{1, 12, -17, -3, -11, -5\\}\n$$\n\n---\n\n### Step 1: Find the mean (average) of the data set\n\n$$\n\\bar{x} = \\frac{1 + 12 + (-17) + (-3) + (-11) + (-5)}{6}\n$$\n\n$$\n\\bar{x} = \\frac{1 + 12 - 17 - 3 - 11 - 5}{6} = \\frac{-21}{6} = -3.5\n$$\n\n---\n\n### Step 2: Compute the squared deviations from the mean\n\n$$\n(1 - (-3.5))^2 = (4.5)^2 = 20.25 \\\\\n(12 - (-3.5))^2 = (15.5)^2 = 240.25 \\\\\n(-17 - (-3.5))^2 = (-13.5)^2 = 182.25 \\\\\n(-3 - (-3.5))^2 = (0.5)^2 = 0.25 \\\\\n(-11 - (-3.5))^2 = (-7.5)^2 = 56.25 \\\\\n(-5 - (-3.5))^2 = (-1.5)^2 = 2.25\n$$\n\n---\n\n### Step 3: Sum the squared deviations\n\n$$\n20.25 + 240.25 + 182.25 + 0.25 + 56.25 + 2.25 = 511.5\n$$\n\n---\n\n### Step 4: Divide by $n - 1$ (sample variance formula)\n\n$$\ns^2 = \\frac{511.5}{6 - 1} = \\frac{511.5}{5} = \\boxed{102.3}\n$$\n\n---\n\n### \u2705 Final Answer:\n\n$$\n\\boxed{102.3}\n$$"
